            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>, <date>Aug. 19, 1863</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Honored Sir: A long time ago I wrote<lb/> to you. I had much to
                write, but I did not<lb/> know whether my writing is agreeable to you.<lb/> That is
                why I am writing to you briefly to<lb/> ask you to send me the “Occident” and<lb/>
                put me down as a subscriber, and, if possible,<lb/> I will gather subscriptions. If
                you have<lb/> written anything about the <placeName>Palestine</placeName>
                Coloniza-<lb/>tion Society, send it to me.<lb/> When I have received the Occident
                more regularly,<lb/> and have made sure of your address, I shall<lb/> send you much
                news, if God grants me<lb/> health. For the present, nothing more.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your devoted servant,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Shimon Berman</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Rev. S. Berman</persName>
            </p>
